I visited the local street food market of "La Floresta" in Quito (Ecuador). I found this large type of berry (Rubus glaucus) called "Mora de Castilla" in Spanish. This is used to produce a traditional Ecuadorian beverage called "Colada Morada": https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Colada_morada)  

There are four different types of "Moras" in Ecuador: Castilla, Brazo, Criolla and Gato

http://www.elcomercio.com/actualidad/negocios/cuatro-tipos-de-moras-pais.html

The "Mora de Castilla" is the most commonly consumed.
